<br>
He made so much noise in all that clunking armour that she had been able to find  him very easily. Stealthily she moved up behind him and whispered in his ear (covered though it was in the strangest shaped helmet she had ever encountered)<br>
'Welcome to Nektulos, young Koada'dal, drop your sword and turn about slowly'<br>
<br>
The young paladin did so and came face to face with his first Teir'dal female.<br>
<br>
'I see your instructors still encourage you to come to our lands and endanger the lives of our young apprentices by attempting to slay our royal guards.'<br>
<br>
She paused as she studied his face. <br>
'Do you not hear the rumours of what I do to those I catch trespassing in my beloved homeland?'<br>
He nodded and squeaked his reply<br>
'We had heard that you were no longer here, that it was safe to venture once more into this foul forest' This last attempt at bravado amused Entice immensly.<br>
<br>
Chuckling in a rather disconcerting way she handed the paladin a peice of parchment, folded and closed with the D'Unnar seal.<br>
<br>
'I shall spare your life on this occasion. Take this letter to Felwith immediately, seek out Vladimirski and give him the letter. I do not expect a reply, but if one is forthcomming bring it to me directly'<br>
------------------------------------<br>
The contents of the letter read as follows:<br>
<br>
Vladimirski, you worthless Paladin,<br>
<br>
A long time has passed has it not since our swords last crossed. I take the blame for this. I confess to having treated you with a grudging respect in the past though you undoubtably are the embodiment of all I despise (and I despise alot).<br>
<br>
This final treachery is beneath even you however. You have brainwashed my husband to leave his home and serve under your 'leadership'. The Elven Elite - ragtag bunch of stragglers of all races though it is (why I even believe you have housed an old pet lizard of mine) is no place for a Warrior and Elder of Neriak, let alone Kenelan D'Unnar, Ambassador to House D'Unnar and, moreover, my husband.<br>
<br>
You would do well to release him into my care at the earliest opportunity. The results of not doing so may well be somewhat undesirable for you and your minions.<br>
<br>
Entice D'Unnar <br>
<br>
