<br>
After he finishes his letter, he summons Wilwen The Hood.<br>
<br>
&quot;Wilwen, please take this cautiosly to Neriak and deliver it secretly to the Lady Entice.  Be wary she doesn't catch you though, she can be, shall we say very evil when scorned.&quot;<br>
<br>
The contents of the letter read as follows:<br>
<br>
Lady Entice,<br>
<br>
So good to see your evilness back in Norrath!  And, Aye it has been a long time since we met.  I have always had respect for you, even though you serve the forces of evil.<br>
<br>
There was no treachery, that is not my way, this you should know by now.  I brainwash no one, all my people serve under their own free will.  I turn very few away whom seek shettle and company in the house of the Elven Elite, except the pure evilness of Shadow Knight and the most evil of all, Necromancers.  My &quot;leadership&quot; is about helping those who seek Truth and Honor for the &quot;good&quot; of Norrath and the lands beyond.<br>
<br>
The lizard you speak of has a name, and that is Carthaz.  He has alwaysseen the way of good.  He grew up with Paladins around him, and was saved at a very young age from the treachery and evilness that prevails in Cabalis.<br>
<br>
All in our guild are free to go anytime they wish, but you would have to convince Kenelan, not myself.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Vladimirski Shadowhunter<BR>
