<br>
As soon as she opened the study door however her humming came to an abrupt finish.<br>
<br>
She sniffed the air..something was not right. Frowning she walked up to her desk and saw a letter propped against her tomes of House records. Closer now to the parchment and the sickly-sweet stench of Feir'dal was unmistakable.<br>
<br>
So early in the morning, and on an empty stomach, Entice felt a brief wave of nausea, and shuddered.<br>
<br>
'urgh',<br>
Snatching up the letter she yelled for one of the house serfs.<br>
'Kraveous... Kraveous... KRAVEOUS!' <br>
<br>
She span round as the door opened and the rather unsightly specimen that was Kraveous shuffled in to her study.<br>
<br>
'M'lady', he managed, bowing awkwardly.<br>
<br>
'Kraveous, remind me please..is or is not this mansion guarded by Neriak's finest, 24 hours a day?'<br>
'ye...'<br>
'How then,' Entice struggled to compose herself 'How then, might I ask, In the name of Innoruuk, can my private rooms be invaded by any Feir'dal that wishes to wander past?' <br>
<br>
Kraveous looked vaccant. <br>
<br>
Ignoring him now Entice opened the letter...a twisted smile playing on her lips as she read.<br>
<br>
...'&quot;Truth and Honour&quot;..deluded fool!...&quot;convince Kenelan&quot;...hah!' Her eyes narrowed as she re-read the letter. <br>
<br>
Kraveous was making for the door quietly when she snapped at him again,<br>
'Where is Qu'el'Velguk?'<br>
<br>
'er..'Kraveous stumbled, unsure of her meaning.<br>
<br>
'Tuard..where is Tuard? Oh never mind. I shall find him myself.' <br>
<br>
She swept out of the room, the door slamming behind her.<br>
<br>
Her mind focused elsewhere she still managed to nod at Lategrey and her young protegee, Jerlys as she met them in the corridor.<br>
'I hear good things about your progress, Jerlys' she said with a warm smile. 'You have a fine mentor'.<br>
<br>
As she marched on at a pace she muttered to herself again..<br>
'&quot; Convince Kenelan&quot;' she smiled..' how little you know me Vladimirski', and continued her search for Tuard. <br>
<br>
